# Configures a 5-byte SPI response cycle before the first loop() call, then
# checks the first transfer sequence: a/b consume bytes 0-1, the buf(3)
# transfer consumes bytes 2-4. Assumes SPI.transfer(buf, len) makes one
# impl_spi_transfer call per byte in order -- adjust if that's not how the
# injected SPI.h overload actually cycles the response buffer.
#
# NOTE: timeline fields are "time, VERB, target, args..." -- SET_RESPONSE is
# the verb, SPI is the target (matching dispatchAction's `target == "SPI"`
# check), not the other way around.
0,   SET_RESPONSE, SPI, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50
0.6, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "a=10 b=20 buf=30,40,50"
